4. AI and Automated Processing
Flight Star uses artificial intelligence, machine learning, and automated tools for certain platform functions, including:
•	AI-generated summaries of crew reviews
•	AI-generated summaries of personal and performance metrics
•	AI moderation assistance
•	AI tagging and categorization

To support these features, we may process and send certain information to AI-related systems or providers, including:
•	review text,
•	ratings,
•	usernames,
•	airline or role,
•	profile information,
•	personal and performance metrics maintained in the platform,
•	and generated prompts.

Private notes are not sent to AI systems based on the information you provided.

We do not use user data to train our own AI models, and we do not permit third-party AI providers to train their general models on Flight Star user content for these features, based on the configuration and understanding you provided.

AI-generated outputs may be automated, may be incomplete or inaccurate, and may not reflect verified facts.

5. Who Can See Your Information
A. Other Subscribed Users
Ratings and written reviews may be visible to other subscribed users within Flight Star.

Crew members referenced on the platform may also be able to see ratings and reviews about them if they access the platform as subscribed users.

B. Favorites
Favorites are visible only to:
•	the user who created them, and
•	Company administration, including the admin and moderator team.

C. Private Notes
Private notes are visible only to:
•	the user who created them, and
•	Company administration, including the admin and moderator team.

For purposes of Flight Star, the admin team and moderator team are the same company administration function. Private notes are not public to other users, but they are not solely local, end-to-end encrypted, or inaccessible to Company administration.

D. Admin and Moderation Access
Company administration may access platform content and related information as needed for:
•	moderation,
•	support,
•	abuse review,
•	account administration,
•	system integrity,
•	enforcement,
•	legal compliance,
•	audits,
•	and defense of claims.

This may include access to reviews, ratings, reports, inbox/outbox messages, attachments, screenshots, favorites, and private notes.

