8. Storage and Retention
We retain personal information for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, including to operate the Services, maintain records, moderate content, enforce agreements, prevent fraud, investigate misuse, support audits, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and establish, exercise, or defend legal claims.

Depending on the nature of the information and the purpose for which it is maintained, some information may be retained for an extended period, including indefinitely where reasonably necessary for legal, operational, audit, safety, fraud-prevention, recordkeeping, or enforcement purposes.

If a user deletes their account, the account may be soft deleted, meaning it may no longer be visible or usable in the app while certain data remains archived in backend systems.

Based on the information provided, archived or retained information after account deletion may include:
•	email address,
•	name,
•	username,
•	auth UID,
•	reviews and ratings posted,
•	moderation history,
•	reports submitted,
•	device, IP, or ban data,
•	timestamps,
•	and backups or logs.

Individual content items may have different deletion behavior in the live application. Based on the information provided:
•	written reviews may be deleted immediately from active use,
•	ratings may be deleted immediately from active use,
•	private notes may be deleted immediately from active use,
•	favorites may be deleted immediately from active use,
•	and report submissions may be deleted immediately from active use.

However, deletion from backups, logs, archives, replicated systems, internal records, or legal hold environments may not be immediate and may not occur where retention is reasonably necessary for the purposes described above.

